  "tldr": [
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/ai",
      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Investigating idiosyncrasies in AI fiction",
      "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.03136",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/hjuopb",
      "score": 4,
      "comments": 2,
      "author": "kehn",
      "published": "2026-07-02T12:02:29Z",
      "bullets": [
        "LLMs display distinct stylistic signatures and repetitive tropes (e.g., 'delve') driven by RLHF alignment and pre-training dataset biases.",
        "Distinctive n-gram distributions and rigid structural patterns make AI-generated fiction highly detectable by statistical and machine learning classifiers.",
        "Overcoming these narrative biases requires specialized fine-tuning, adjusted frequency penalties, and dynamic temperature sampling during inference."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "If you’re a button, you have one job",
      "url": "https://unsung.aresluna.org/if-youre-a-button-you-have-one-job/",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/zhizsf",
      "score": 12,
      "comments": 8,
      "author": "noncrab",
      "published": "2026-07-05T08:24:06Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Use semantic HTML <button> elements instead of styled <div> tags to inherit native keyboard navigation and accessibility behaviors.",
        "Avoid using anchor tags with href=\"#\" for JavaScript triggers; use <button type=\"button\"> to prevent broken navigation behaviors.",
        "Native button elements eliminate the need to write custom event listeners for Enter and Space key interactions."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/security",
      "category": "security",
      "title": "Bad Epoll (CVE-2026-46242)",
      "url": "https://github.com/J-jaeyoung/bad-epoll",
      "discuss_url": "https://lobste.rs/s/drf6my",
      "score": 40,
      "comments": 11,
      "author": "dzwdz",
      "published": "2026-07-04T18:40:12Z",
      "bullets": [
        "CVE-2026-46242 identifies a critical vulnerability in the Linux kernel's epoll subsystem, potentially enabling local privilege escalation.",
        "Security teams should prioritize patching host kernels, as epoll flaws often allow attackers to escape containerized environments.",
        "The vulnerability likely stems from race conditions or use-after-free issues during concurrent I/O event multiplexing."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/devops",
      "category": "devops",
      "title": "I Don't Maintain My Homelab",
      "url": "https://cleberg.net/blog/homelab-maintenance.html",
